cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper analyzes the incidence of text "reuse" in scientific articles deposited to arXiv.org, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis involves measuring the global frequencies of text reuse, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) or cybersecurity (cs.CY) as well. Additionally, the paper considers the distribution of countries of origin of articles containing large amounts of reused text, which could relate to cryptography (cs.CR).
